item.title: [HBASE-7392] Disable failing example unit tests TestZooKeeperScanPolicyObserver and TestBulkDeleteProtocol
item.description:
Jenkins run https://builds.apache.org/job/HBase-TRUNK/3638/ turned up two broke example tests. They pass on a jdk6 machine locally but not on my jdk7 laptop. Somethings up. My guess is that these failures have been there a while but only surfaced because we got further than we normally do on a jenkins run.

Tests have no output on jenkins.

If I run w/

$ MAVEN_OPTS=" -Xmx3g" mvn test -PlocalTests -Dtest=TestBulkDeleteProtocol -Dtest.output.tofile=false

item.summary: Disable failing example unit tests TestZooKeeperScanPolicyObserver and TestBulkDeleteProtocol

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: Here is patch to disable the two failing tests.

TestRowCountEndpoint, also an example, passed on jenkins but failed locally for me so it is likely not just a jdk7 thing.

Will wait before applying to see if these fails happen again up on a jenkins run.
Hmm.. Looks like Anoop changed or removed his JIRA account.

Hmm... We need to fix these tests. There is no reason why these should not work with JDK7.
TestZooKeeperScanPolicyObserver passes fine locally in 0.94 with (Open)JDK7.

So something's else is up. Let's not just disabling these.
Lars Hofhansl jdk7 is red herring I'd say.

Andrew.. No I am using the same old account.
Stack I will have a look at it... Will check with JDK7
TestBulkDeleteProtocol and TestRowCountEndpoint having Endpoint execution. TestZooKeeperScanPolicyObserver is having normal table ops.

Looks like the failure is related to simultaneous execution of more than one test.
fwiw, the test execution order is random with jdk 1.7 and JUnit < 4.11. It's not random anymore with junit 4.11 nor with jdk 1.6
This issue prevents trunk artifacts from being generated.
Marking down to major. HBASE-7994 disabled these example tests in 0.95.
Subsumed by hbase-7994 which disabled all example unit tests.
